benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/catalog/xml - Upload the full catalog as XML

covered: POST Valid Payload scenarios cover successful uploads with required and optional headers across TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC11, TC13, TC14, TC21, TC22, TC24, TC25, TC26, TC27, TC28, TC29, TC30, TC31.

Input validation and error handling is well covered via tests for missing headers (TC06), empty headers (TC07), malformed/malformed payloads (TC08), empty body (TC09), whitespace-only payload (TC23), partially corrupted payload (TC18), malicious content (TC17), and invalid content type (TC10).
Resilience and reliability scenarios are tested for network interruption (TC15) and backend service down (TC16).
Performance/load considerations are addressed with TC19 (normal load) and TC20 (concurrent load).

Security, compatibility, and edge-case coverage are addressed via authentication tests (TC14), duplicate version (TC25), regression tests (TC21, TC22), encoding tests (TC29), whitespace/unicode (TC24), boundary values (TC30), and accessibility (TC31).
gaps: No explicit 500 Internal Server Error scenario to simulate generic server/database failures.
No explicit rate-limiting/throttling tests to validate behavior under burst traffic.
Caching behavior for POST responses (e.g., ETag or Cache-Control) is not tested.
Location header verification is not consistently asserted across all successful scenarios (only some test cases explicitly check it).
Tests for content negotiation edge cases (Accept header variations) are not present.
recommendations: Add a 500 Internal Server Error scenario to verify handling of backend/database failures.
Introduce rate-limiting/throttling tests to validate behavior under high request rates.
Add tests for caching headers on POST responses where applicable, and verify Cache-Control/ETag semantics.
Ensure Location header presence and correctness is asserted in all successful POST scenarios, not just a subset.
Consider additional content-type boundary tests (charset variations, missing charset) to strengthen payload validation.
